Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will face questions relating to state capture, gender-based violence, as well as whether the ongoing political crisis in SA is caused by the absence of moral and ethical leadership. CAPE TOWN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa faces questions relating to state capture and gender-based violence in the National Assembly. He'll also be asked whether the ongoing political crisis in the country is caused by the absence of moral and ethical leadership. This is Ramaphosa's last oral reply session for this quarter before the National Assembly takes a recess. WATCH: Cyril Rampaphosa in Parliament